    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so my tomato plants are acting weird. the leaves on the bottom are turning kinda yellow and pale compared to the top ones. what's probably going on with them?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yellowing lower leaves on tomato plants, especially when the tops look fine, often points to a nutrient deficiency, most commonly nitrogen. Nitrogen is a mobile nutrient, meaning the plant moves it from older, lower leaves to support new growth at the top. You might also be experiencing watering issues, either overwatering or underwatering, which can stress the lower foliage. It's a good idea to check your soil moisture and consider a balanced fertilizer application.",
