    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for the info. i think it might be the nitrogen then. how do i actually fix the soil to get more of it in there? do i need to change the pH or something?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To boost nitrogen levels, you can apply a nitrogen-rich fertilizer, like one containing ammonium nitrate or blood meal, directly to the soil around the base of the plants. You don't necessarily need to change the pH immediately, but if your soil is very acidic or alkaline, it can lock up nutrients, so a simple soil test would be helpful. For a quick fix, a liquid fish emulsion can provide a gentle nitrogen boost. Remember to water thoroughly after applying any fertilizer to help it distribute evenly.",
