    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "makes sense. i'll try the blood meal. i'm also worried that something in the soil is actively stripping the nutrients away. like, is there anything that causes that kind of rapid depletion?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Rapid nutrient depletion, or leaching, is often caused by excessive watering, which washes soluble nutrients past the roots. Another culprit is an overabundance of certain microbes or fungi that are aggressively consuming available minerals in the soil. If your soil is compacted, it can also impede root function, making nutrient uptake difficult, like a slow, constant drain. Sometimes, even certain fertilizers, if overapplied, can create conditions that encourage nutrient lockout.",
      "source": "target",
